  "texts": [
    "AE opens possibilities for hypothesis generation and datafeasibility of projects, altering the traditional inductive nature of scientific research -in which a problem is followed by a literature review to formulate a question, which then guides the construction of a method, and finally testing to achieve results.",
    "Since AE experts see this model as inefficient, building robust platforms capable of running experiments autonomously, and aiming to accelerate scientific discovery, requires broader public debate regarding its implications to society [136].Until the present, AE development has adhered to existing research ethics guidelines and regulations.",
    "As societal awareness of AE grows, novel ethical questions and regulatory considerations can be expected.",
    "More empirical research is needed to support the creation of effective ethical guidelines and policy recommendations for AE innovation.",
    "Due to the novelty of AE in science and medicine, it can benefit from international collaboration concerning ethical aspects and societal impacts."
  ]
}